ChEA: transcription factor regulation inferred from integrating genome-wide ChIP-X experiments.
ENCODE: Encyclopedia of DNA Elements
ARCHS4: Massive Mining of Publicly Available RNA-seq Data from Human and Mouse
TRRUST: Transcription Regulatory Relationships Unraveled by Sentence-based Text Mining
JASPAR is the largest open-access database of curated and non-redundant transcription factor (TF) binding profiles from six different taxonomic groups.
The NIH Roadmap Epigenomics Mapping Consortium was launched with the goal of producing a public resource of human epigenomic data to catalyze basic biology and disease-oriented research. 
TargetScan: In bioinformatics, TargetScan is a web server that predicts biological targets of microRNAs (miRNAs) by searching for the presence of sites that match the seed region of each miRNA.
miRTarBase: the experimentally validated microRNA-target interactions database
